Description: Wrapper of the C++ model FATE. FATE is a vegetation model based on Plant Functional Groups 
    (PFG) that aims to simulate primary ecological succession through entities interactions, 
    population dynamics and dispersal, and external drivers such as disturbance regimes or environmental variations.
    RFate is a package which provides functions to :
        1) gather, prepare and format data to be used with FATE ;
        2) run FATE simulation(s)
        3) process and analyze data produced by FATE.
